digging a generous amount of compost. then dig a 10 trench. Form mounds of soil at the bottom of the trench about 12in apart. Set each crown on top of a mound and drape the roots over the mound like a wig over a head. This enables the roots to establish themselves faster as they will get even moisture and nutrients. The crowns should be at least 2-3 below the soil surface"
